If you want to increase availability to the general public, you have to limit it. 

- Nvidia Direct Sales Only
- Anti-bot measures such as Captcha  (this would do wonders for e-tailers, it's why all the cards get snatched up in a matter of seconds....)
- Multi-Factor Identity Verification (SSI and Photo ID Requirements etc...)
- 1-2 per person

You can put limiters on the cards all you want but unless you actually implement measures to make it difficult for miners to acquire large quantities of cards then we're not getting anywhere.
